WEBVTT

00:00.167 --> 00:02.169
(male narrator)
Previously on "Pretty Little
Liars, The Perfectionists.."

00:02.169 --> 00:04.213
I did it to protect you
and your family.

00:04.213 --> 00:06.882
- From Nolan?
- You wanted him gone too, Cait.

00:06.882 --> 00:08.842
(Taylor)
Someone hijacked Beacon Guard
to spy

00:08.842 --> 00:10.719
on a select group of people
at BHU.

00:10.719 --> 00:12.095
I never figured out
who they were.

00:12.095 --> 00:13.972
I promised my dad
I wouldn't tell anyone.

00:13.972 --> 00:15.974
You can't be defined
by one mistake.

00:15.974 --> 00:17.601
(Dylan)
Yeah, unless you cheat at BHU.

00:17.601 --> 00:19.686
I was there
when my dad was shot.

00:19.686 --> 00:22.022
I saw it all
and I still see it every day.

00:22.022 --> 00:24.274
I'm so sorry. A friend of mine
needs help. I'll be right back.

00:24.274 --> 00:26.109
- That's Lee Redmond.
- The Manhattan gallery owner?

00:26.109 --> 00:27.986
Don't waste your shot,
lead with your passion

00:27.986 --> 00:31.240
you wear it on your sleeve,
Zach.

00:31.240 --> 00:32.991
A member of my staff is having

00:32.991 --> 00:35.869
an inappropriate relationship
with a student.

00:35.869 --> 00:37.537
- Really?
- You're terminated.

00:37.537 --> 00:39.248
- Dana has your money.
- What?

00:39.248 --> 00:42.000
(Taylor)
Jeremy was walking
toward Thorne Hall

00:42.000 --> 00:43.335
moments before the blackout.

00:43.335 --> 00:44.544
He killed Nolan.

00:44.544 --> 00:45.879
If I tell the police what I did

00:45.879 --> 00:47.923
then my life will be over,
and so will yours.

00:47.923 --> 00:49.216
You're not going anywhere.

00:49.216 --> 00:51.343
I trusted you.

00:51.343 --> 00:53.387
[gunshot]

00:53.387 --> 00:55.013
He was running towards you.

00:55.013 --> 00:57.224
And Taylor was afraid
for her life. We all saw it.

00:59.017 --> 01:00.936
You were afraid.

01:00.936 --> 01:02.312
He's alive!

01:02.312 --> 01:04.523
[dramatic music]

01:06.024 --> 01:08.944
[siren wailing]

01:10.195 --> 01:12.114
[indistinct chatter on radio]

01:12.114 --> 01:15.033
[siren wailing]

01:15.033 --> 01:18.370
- It was self-defense.
- Jeremy attacked Taylor.

01:18.370 --> 01:20.622
So she shot him
to protect herself.

01:20.622 --> 01:22.124
Why would he wanna hurt Taylor?

01:22.124 --> 01:25.585
Taylor wouldn't let him escape,
so he came after her.

01:25.585 --> 01:28.046
- Jeremy killed Nolan.
- Why?

01:33.677 --> 01:37.764
Ah, he was my boyfriend
while I was dating Nolan.

01:38.974 --> 01:41.059
Jeremy wanted me
to break it off with him

01:41.059 --> 01:43.061
but I wasn't ready.

01:43.061 --> 01:45.647
Jeremy told me what he did.

01:45.647 --> 01:47.733
He wanted me to go away
with him tonight

01:47.733 --> 01:49.443
'but I-I told my friends
to come here'

01:49.443 --> 01:51.987
so we can just try
to convince him..

01:51.987 --> 01:54.489
...to do the right thing
and turn himself in.

01:54.489 --> 01:56.992
No one expected him
to go after Taylor.

01:56.992 --> 01:59.036
(Ava)
Jeremy was stalkin' Nolan.

01:59.036 --> 02:01.913
Taylor found proof.
It's all here.

02:05.584 --> 02:07.127
Is Taylor okay?

02:07.127 --> 02:09.671
Luckily, a family friend
was at the gala tonight.

02:09.671 --> 02:11.548
Dr. Benson's taking her
to a retreat.

02:11.548 --> 02:13.550
She's in good care.

02:14.718 --> 02:17.095
Taylor told me everything.

02:17.095 --> 02:19.556
I can't thank you all enough
for what you did to protect

02:19.556 --> 02:22.893
my daughter and to expose
the man who murdered my son.

02:24.895 --> 02:27.814
I hope you'll accept my apology
for believing

02:27.814 --> 02:30.567
that you had anything to do
with Nolan's death.

02:32.027 --> 02:37.074
I was blinded by grief
and I, uh, put my trust..

02:37.074 --> 02:38.867
...in the wrong hands.

02:41.745 --> 02:45.540
- We're just glad it's over.
- Thank you again.

02:50.087 --> 02:52.964
What you did
to try to tear us apart..

02:52.964 --> 02:54.758
...it brought us
closer together.

02:54.758 --> 02:57.844
And it made us stronger.

02:57.844 --> 03:00.055
You've got a name forever.

03:07.521 --> 03:09.648
Let's go home.

03:14.569 --> 03:20.492
♪ If I show you then I know
you won't tell what I said ♪

03:20.492 --> 03:26.540
♪ 'Cause two can keep a secret
if one of them is dead ♪♪

03:28.834 --> 03:30.919
(Caitlin)
I'm calling to check
the status of a patient.

03:30.919 --> 03:32.671
- 'The name, please.'
- Jeremy Beckett.

03:32.671 --> 03:34.589
(woman on phone)
'One moment.'

03:42.305 --> 03:44.724
Do you need help packing?

03:44.724 --> 03:46.143
'We're getting picked up
at 5:00.'

03:46.143 --> 03:47.853
I'm not going to DC with you.

03:47.853 --> 03:50.230
It is not a punishment, Caitlin.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.899
It's a chance to take a breath
and reset your life.

03:52.899 --> 03:54.651
Call it what you want.

03:54.651 --> 03:56.403
You're forcing me to do
something I don't wanna do.

03:56.403 --> 03:58.488
We're doing this
because we love you.

03:58.488 --> 03:59.948
And we're worried.

03:59.948 --> 04:01.533
I don't know
what's going on with you

04:01.533 --> 04:03.785
but you're not yourself.

04:03.785 --> 04:05.829
You had a secret boyfriend

04:05.829 --> 04:09.166
who killed Nolan Hotchkiss
for you.

04:09.166 --> 04:12.586
Caitlin,
it's a lot to deal with.

04:12.586 --> 04:14.880
- You can't wanna stay here.
- But I do.

04:14.880 --> 04:17.549
Because this is where
your friends are?

04:17.549 --> 04:21.595
The daughter
of one of the FBI's most wanted?

04:21.595 --> 04:23.972
And a student
who committed academic fraud?

04:23.972 --> 04:26.475
Actually, Ava's a rising star
in the fashion industry

04:26.475 --> 04:27.976
and Dylan's a music prodigy.

04:27.976 --> 04:30.812
I've arranged for you to be
Senator Hastings' summer intern.

04:30.812 --> 04:32.564
You'll start at Georgetown
after the holidays

04:32.564 --> 04:34.232
and you'll see a therapist
twice a week.

04:34.232 --> 04:35.734
A therapist?

04:35.734 --> 04:37.444
You have to admit
that you're lost, Caitlin.

04:37.444 --> 04:40.405
You can't force me to leave BHU.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.073
You're right.

04:42.073 --> 04:44.993
'But if you stay, you'll be
completely on your own.'

04:44.993 --> 04:47.787
You won't be living here and
we won't be paying for school.

04:50.081 --> 04:51.917
♪ I wait for you.. ♪

04:51.917 --> 04:54.294
When I walked away from
the "Vogue" editor yesterday

04:54.294 --> 04:55.921
to talk to you

04:55.921 --> 04:57.255
she didn't think
that I was being rude.

04:57.255 --> 04:59.174
Julie Katchen was impressed.

04:59.174 --> 05:01.551
She said that giving up
my chance to talk to her

05:01.551 --> 05:03.637
to help a friend
is what actually made me

05:03.637 --> 05:05.055
"Vogue" material.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.097
Well, congrats.

05:06.097 --> 05:09.059
And, uh, is that what we are?

05:09.059 --> 05:10.644
Friends?

05:12.354 --> 05:14.606
I don't know, Fortson.

05:14.606 --> 05:15.982
You tell me.

05:15.982 --> 05:18.318
Maybe we can figure it out
this summer in New York.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.945
No way.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.696
You were holding out on me.
You got the exhibit?

05:21.696 --> 05:24.449
- Yeah.
- Zach, that's huge!

05:24.449 --> 05:25.909
Yeah, it's huge.

05:25.909 --> 05:28.787
And I want to thank you
for pushing me to talk to Lee.

05:28.787 --> 05:30.956
She thinks
I have a lot of potential.

05:32.749 --> 05:34.876
Well, what just happened?
We're happy, right?

05:34.876 --> 05:37.462
Just whenever things start to go
the way they're supposed to go

05:37.462 --> 05:40.090
I get nervous.

05:40.090 --> 05:42.384
Usually it means something
bad's about to happen.

05:42.384 --> 05:44.719
Nothing bad is gonna happen.

05:44.719 --> 05:48.056
This is all good...
for both of us.

05:48.056 --> 05:51.476
So if I am going to New York
this summer

05:51.476 --> 05:53.895
I'm going to need a job
to pay for it

05:53.895 --> 05:54.938
or two or three like you

05:54.938 --> 05:57.983
so can you put in a good word
for me?

05:57.983 --> 06:00.735
- I thought you had money.
- Not anymore.

06:01.945 --> 06:05.073
But that's okay.
I will work to pay my way.

06:07.617 --> 06:08.910
I don't need to wait
until this summer

06:08.910 --> 06:11.705
to figure out what we are.

06:11.705 --> 06:14.749
- I know what I want.
- Yeah?

06:14.749 --> 06:16.918
(male #1)
'You workin' or not, Fortson?'

06:18.128 --> 06:19.921
Find you later.

06:24.217 --> 06:26.303
(Andrew)
'Now that they've caught
Nolan's killer'

06:26.303 --> 06:28.013
thanks to you and your friends

06:28.013 --> 06:30.682
and you've been given
a rare second chance

06:30.682 --> 06:33.143
by the ethics committee,
thanks to Claire

06:33.143 --> 06:35.186
I say we put
all that stuff behind us

06:35.186 --> 06:37.772
and start planning our summer
in Seattle.

06:39.107 --> 06:40.817
I just can't believe it.
I mean, Mr. Hale

06:40.817 --> 06:42.360
actually used the B word.

06:42.360 --> 06:45.780
He said that my, I mean, our..

06:45.780 --> 06:47.449
...your song was brilliant.

06:47.449 --> 06:50.577
He said there's no way you're
not getting that internship.

06:50.577 --> 06:55.957
Thank you for taking a chance
on me and for loving me.

06:58.084 --> 07:00.837
I believe
I'm the luckiest guy at BHU.

07:12.849 --> 07:14.184
It's not fair
that Claire gives everybody

07:14.184 --> 07:16.102
a second chance,
but you have to leave.

07:16.102 --> 07:19.147
Claire made it clear there are
some things she can't forgive.

07:19.147 --> 07:21.608
Sleeping with a student
is one of them.

07:21.608 --> 07:23.693
There was no talking her
out of this.

07:23.693 --> 07:25.987
What sucks is that
I loved this job.

07:25.987 --> 07:27.238
And what's even worse is

07:27.238 --> 07:29.074
I'll never find out
what that list was.

07:29.074 --> 07:30.283
The list?

07:30.283 --> 07:32.035
When I got locked out
of the system, remember?

07:32.035 --> 07:34.454
You, Ray Hogadorn and Caitlin.

07:34.454 --> 07:35.830
Someone was using
my admissions code

07:35.830 --> 07:37.707
to generate a list
of some sort.

07:37.707 --> 07:39.876
I'm sorry, Mona.

07:39.876 --> 07:42.003
Some puzzles are just
not meant to be solved.

07:42.003 --> 07:43.505
Do you know
what that sounds like to me?

07:43.505 --> 07:47.092
It's like telling a kid
they can never have candy again.

07:47.092 --> 07:49.844
Maybe getting out of here
isn't such a bad thing.

07:49.844 --> 07:52.389
Let's face it.
This town breeds drama.

07:52.389 --> 07:54.724
Think about Taylor and
everything she's been through.

07:54.724 --> 07:57.519
Well, she's having a nice rest
at Riverwell.

07:57.519 --> 07:58.853
I checked it out online.

07:58.853 --> 08:01.523
Looks like a touchy,
feely place to regroup.

08:01.523 --> 08:04.234
Doesn't sound so bad to me.

08:04.234 --> 08:07.821
I came here for what I thought
was for the right reasons, but..

08:07.821 --> 08:10.240
...sure has been a bumpy road.

08:10.240 --> 08:11.991
So you think
you're on the wrong path?

08:11.991 --> 08:14.285
It never fails.

08:14.285 --> 08:16.162
Ever since high school,
I feel like I've been heading

08:16.162 --> 08:19.666
toward a dead end or drivin'
a whirly car off of a cliff.

08:24.254 --> 08:25.839
When I booked
my ticket to Philly

08:25.839 --> 08:28.091
the aisle seat next to me
was still available.

08:28.091 --> 08:30.051
If you're serious
about not staying.

08:30.051 --> 08:32.053
This was supposed to be
my fresh start.

08:32.053 --> 08:35.140
My chance to prove
that I could change.

08:35.140 --> 08:36.433
But every time
I look in the mirror

08:36.433 --> 08:38.101
all I see is a divorced woman

08:38.101 --> 08:40.645
who until last night
was a murder suspect.

08:40.645 --> 08:43.064
Window or aisle?

08:47.402 --> 08:50.989
♪ 'Cause I see you like
you like what you see ♪

08:50.989 --> 08:53.575
It's not just me, right?
People are staring at us.

08:53.575 --> 08:56.119
Yeah. Well, I guess
we're the talk of the school.

08:56.119 --> 08:59.122
Nolan's perfect posse
catches his killer.

08:59.122 --> 09:00.206
It's a headline grabber.

09:00.206 --> 09:02.167
Well, it didn't help
with me and my mom.

09:02.167 --> 09:04.669
If I don't go to DC with her,
she's cutting me off.

09:04.669 --> 09:07.213
There's no way I can go home.

09:07.213 --> 09:10.717
You can stay with us.
If sleeping on a couch is okay.

09:10.717 --> 09:11.968
Are you sure Andrew won't mind?

09:11.968 --> 09:13.720
He'll be okay with it.

09:13.720 --> 09:15.221
He is my best friend.

09:15.221 --> 09:18.475
I haven't had a best friend
since Betsy Burnham.

09:18.475 --> 09:21.102
The Little Mermaid who tried
to light your hair on fire?

09:21.102 --> 09:23.313
Mm-hmm, over a KitKat bar.

09:24.397 --> 09:26.065
[cellphone chimes]

09:27.817 --> 09:29.652
[sighs]
It's about Jeremy.

09:29.652 --> 09:31.529
I put an alert on my phone.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.072
"His condition has been upgraded

09:33.072 --> 09:34.616
"but he's still refusing
to talk to anyone

09:34.616 --> 09:36.034
not even a lawyer."

09:36.034 --> 09:37.243
Even if he does decide to talk

09:37.243 --> 09:38.661
no one will believe him.

09:38.661 --> 09:41.247
He killed Nolan,
that's what matters.

09:41.247 --> 09:44.042
Is it terrible
that I still care about him?

09:44.042 --> 09:45.919
What he did to Nolan
was horrific

09:45.919 --> 09:48.213
but he did it for me.

09:48.213 --> 09:50.089
I can't just turn off
my emotions like a switch

09:50.089 --> 09:52.383
and not care about him.

09:52.383 --> 09:54.803
Nothing in the world
is ever black and white.

09:54.803 --> 09:57.055
Or just good or bad.

09:57.055 --> 09:59.099
Things just aren't
that easy for us.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.892
We want it all
and we're willing to work for it

10:00.892 --> 10:03.895
but it comes at a price.

10:03.895 --> 10:05.313
(Luke)
'Next?'

10:05.313 --> 10:06.189
♪ 'Cause you liking
what you see ♪

10:06.189 --> 10:07.774
♪ You know you like it ♪♪

10:07.774 --> 10:10.276
[dramatic music]

10:12.195 --> 10:14.364
- I have to get out of here.
- Hey, wait.

10:14.364 --> 10:15.782
Dylan.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.245
- What's wrong?
- Dylan, breathe.

10:20.245 --> 10:23.081
I went to high school
with that guy.

10:23.081 --> 10:24.415
He bullied me for being gay.

10:24.415 --> 10:27.252
He is the reason that I left
and I never looked back.

10:27.252 --> 10:29.170
And now he's here.

10:41.558 --> 10:43.142
[sighs]

10:44.477 --> 10:46.312
[dramatic music]

10:47.730 --> 10:48.982
Dad?

10:54.320 --> 10:55.446
Ava.

10:56.906 --> 10:58.241
Dad.

11:03.371 --> 11:05.373
How have you been? You okay?

11:07.041 --> 11:09.085
Mom finally let you
grow a beard.

11:09.085 --> 11:11.421
I had to change my look
to come and see you.

11:14.007 --> 11:16.217
Your mom and I wanna come home.

11:16.217 --> 11:17.969
Dad, there's nothing that
I would want more in the world

11:17.969 --> 11:20.138
but you shouldn't be here.

11:21.931 --> 11:23.933
Dana Booker
is the head of security.

11:23.933 --> 11:26.811
Ava, what I did was wrong

11:26.811 --> 11:29.063
and I have a plan
to make things right.

11:29.063 --> 11:31.149
I still have most of the money
and if I return it

11:31.149 --> 11:33.109
they'll limit my jail time.

11:33.109 --> 11:35.862
I have to start from scratch,
but..

11:35.862 --> 11:38.114
...it will be
with a clean slate.

11:38.114 --> 11:40.408
Are you here
because you need my help?

11:40.408 --> 11:42.327
A courier
will drop a package off

11:42.327 --> 11:44.120
on your campus mailbox
this afternoon.

11:44.120 --> 11:46.539
It will be sealed
for legal reasons.

11:46.539 --> 11:49.417
This is what I need to start
paying back the money.

11:49.417 --> 11:51.794
You'll get a text
when the papers arrive.

11:51.794 --> 11:53.379
Dad..

11:55.840 --> 11:58.092
...the money you left me..

12:00.219 --> 12:02.347
...we can't pay that back.

12:02.347 --> 12:04.432
Booker found it.
She hasn't turned it in yet

12:04.432 --> 12:05.642
but I think
she's keeping it for herself.

12:05.642 --> 12:08.353
Let's not get sucked
into Booker's game, okay?

12:08.353 --> 12:11.022
It's a distraction.
It's what she wants.

12:11.022 --> 12:14.442
Okay.
I'll do whatever I can to help.

12:14.442 --> 12:17.612
- I love you.
- I love you too.

12:23.451 --> 12:25.370
My beautiful dreamer.

12:28.122 --> 12:30.124
Dad, be careful.

12:36.506 --> 12:38.466
Just when I think
I'm getting my life together

12:38.466 --> 12:41.302
he's here and it's like I'm 14
all over again.

12:41.302 --> 12:42.971
Afraid to show my face at school
because that guy's

12:42.971 --> 12:44.514
gonna make my life
a living hell.

12:44.514 --> 12:46.474
Don't be so hard on yourself.

12:46.474 --> 12:49.978
Being gay in high school
was traumatic.

12:49.978 --> 12:51.729
Even for me, growing up in LA.

12:51.729 --> 12:53.398
And considering everything
that's happened to you lately--

12:53.398 --> 12:55.400
I'm not doing this again,
alright? I refuse.

12:55.400 --> 12:57.527
I need to confront him
and I need Luke to know

12:57.527 --> 13:00.571
that I'm not gonna
take his crap anymore.

13:00.571 --> 13:02.657
Would it help
if I came with you?

13:05.159 --> 13:08.037
- Honestly, it would.
- Then I'll be there.

13:10.581 --> 13:12.166
[knock on door]

13:17.296 --> 13:19.340
May I come in?

13:21.759 --> 13:23.678
What do you want?

13:25.596 --> 13:27.974
Earlier today,
an unidentified man

13:27.974 --> 13:30.768
showed up on Beacon Guard.

13:30.768 --> 13:32.437
He entered your building.

13:32.437 --> 13:36.607
6'1", 160 pounds, black parka.

13:36.607 --> 13:38.234
Sound familiar?

13:38.234 --> 13:41.320
No. Should it?

13:41.320 --> 13:43.281
I'm not gonna ask you
if your dad was here.

13:43.281 --> 13:46.034
I don't wanna make you
lie to me.

13:46.034 --> 13:48.453
I embarrassed Claire Hotchkiss.

13:48.453 --> 13:50.496
It's only a matter of time
until she fires me.

13:50.496 --> 13:53.458
I want back in the FBI
and you're broke.

13:53.458 --> 13:56.210
There's a way
we can fix both our problems.

13:56.210 --> 13:58.254
Turn in your dad
and I'll give your money back.

13:58.254 --> 14:00.590
It's as simple as that.

14:00.590 --> 14:02.592
I don't know what money
you're talking about.

14:02.592 --> 14:05.136
It's some of the money
your dad stole.

14:05.136 --> 14:07.805
You've been using it
to pay your tuition..

14:07.805 --> 14:09.932
...which is a felony.

14:09.932 --> 14:13.686
Well, if you could prove that,
I doubt you'd be standing here.

14:13.686 --> 14:16.522
Why is he here?
Why take the risk?

14:17.482 --> 14:19.233
I can't help you.

14:19.233 --> 14:20.568
[mobile chimes]

14:25.573 --> 14:28.493
Zach wanted you to know
that Crimson Cafe is hirin'.

14:31.079 --> 14:32.997
Did you know
the FBI believes your father

14:32.997 --> 14:36.667
is only in possession
of half of the money he stole?

14:36.667 --> 14:39.128
'What's in your little bag
is just a drop in a bucket.'

14:41.255 --> 14:42.799
Whatever you say, Dana.

14:42.799 --> 14:46.469
I think he's back to get
the rest of what he stole.

14:46.469 --> 14:48.763
You're a smart girl, Ava.

14:48.763 --> 14:50.598
I'm giving you the dots.

14:50.598 --> 14:52.850
'Connect them.'

14:52.850 --> 14:55.645
Or I'll turn that bag of money
in to the authorities

14:55.645 --> 14:57.814
and they'll have
a lot of questions for you.

15:08.282 --> 15:09.742
[knock on door]

15:09.742 --> 15:11.619
Oh, those are probably the boxes
I ordered.

15:11.619 --> 15:13.704
I haven't even started
packing my games.

15:15.665 --> 15:17.166
Hi, Mason.

15:20.837 --> 15:24.507
- I was, uh, just leaving.
- No, you weren't.

15:28.594 --> 15:31.222
So I take it
she knows about us?

15:32.557 --> 15:35.476
We're not an us,
and you have to go.

15:35.476 --> 15:37.186
Well, not until you tell me
what's goin' on.

15:37.186 --> 15:39.605
I'm leaving. I got fired.

15:40.815 --> 15:43.401
Why? What happened?

15:44.986 --> 15:47.321
Claire found out about us.

15:48.698 --> 15:50.533
Stop packing.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.579
You're not going anywhere.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.880
[dramatic music]

16:33.117 --> 16:35.494
Oh, my God.
My mom's already cut me off.

16:35.494 --> 16:37.496
- I got this.
- Thanks.

16:37.496 --> 16:42.710
♪ That's two in the bag
for her ♪

16:42.710 --> 16:47.215
♪ Or three if you
count the other week.. ♪♪

16:47.215 --> 16:49.091
You got one of those, too, huh?

16:49.091 --> 16:51.969
Crimson Society, the envelope.

16:51.969 --> 16:53.804
What does it mean?

16:53.804 --> 16:55.640
Well, rumor has it,
back in the day

16:55.640 --> 16:58.100
there was a secret society
at BHU.

16:58.100 --> 17:00.394
- Like Skull and Bones?
- Exactly.

17:00.394 --> 17:01.854
The older generation of alumnus
would select

17:01.854 --> 17:03.814
the best
and the brightest students.

17:03.814 --> 17:06.525
It's an open door
to power and influence.

17:06.525 --> 17:08.236
They can make your dreams
come true.

17:08.236 --> 17:11.239
Like if you had
an internship at "Vogue"

17:11.239 --> 17:12.823
but had no way
of paying for it?

17:12.823 --> 17:14.116
Exactly.

17:14.116 --> 17:17.036
Or if you needed financial help
to stay at BHU

17:17.036 --> 17:18.537
you'd have their support.

17:18.537 --> 17:20.039
So that's your plan B.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.624
[cell phone chimes]

17:23.584 --> 17:26.045
Sorry, I have to run.
Thank you for the coffee.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.506
But you paid. Ava.

17:32.927 --> 17:35.638
I have to be honest, Caitlin.

17:35.638 --> 17:37.515
Of course, you should apply.

17:37.515 --> 17:40.226
But they give financial aid
to people in need

17:40.226 --> 17:42.687
and your family is not
in that lower income bracket.

17:42.687 --> 17:45.606
If my parents cut me off, I'll
be in the zero income bracket.

17:45.606 --> 17:48.651
But you have the opportunity
to go to Georgetown.

17:48.651 --> 17:50.611
That's a great school.

17:50.611 --> 17:52.113
But it's not BHU.

17:52.113 --> 17:53.489
After everything
that's happened

17:53.489 --> 17:54.782
why do you wanna stay?

17:54.782 --> 17:57.118
A year ago, I-I would have said
I wanted to stay

17:57.118 --> 17:58.953
for the same reasons we all do.

17:58.953 --> 18:00.705
If you can succeed
in this pressure cooker

18:00.705 --> 18:03.791
you can succeed anywhere,
and people know it.

18:03.791 --> 18:04.917
But that's changed?

18:04.917 --> 18:06.502
You said it was important
when I met you

18:06.502 --> 18:08.504
but now I know it's really true.

18:08.504 --> 18:10.881
I've finally got friends
who are like family.

18:15.177 --> 18:17.305
I've been known to be wrong.

18:18.472 --> 18:20.891
You're kind of a Debbie Downer
as an advisor.

18:21.934 --> 18:24.353
I'm sorry, I..

18:24.353 --> 18:27.982
You've caught me
in a reflective life moment.

18:27.982 --> 18:31.819
I shouldn't be advising anyone
about anything right now.

18:31.819 --> 18:34.322
I've done enough
to screw you guys up already.

18:34.322 --> 18:35.990
Your actions
are unconventional

18:35.990 --> 18:38.743
but because of you,
we're all still here.

18:38.743 --> 18:40.870
You think I'm unconventional?

18:43.247 --> 18:44.957
When I was a little girl

18:44.957 --> 18:48.377
my moms used to take me
to boxing matches.

18:48.377 --> 18:51.881
Uh, looking back on it,
it's pretty weird.

18:51.881 --> 18:54.842
[laughs]
But I remember this one guy

18:54.842 --> 18:57.053
and they called him
an unconventional fighter.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.805
'I mean, everything about the
way he boxed was unorthodox'

18:59.805 --> 19:01.932
'and he wasn't pretty to watch.'

19:01.932 --> 19:04.852
'But he won because the other
guy never knew what was coming.'

19:05.936 --> 19:09.065
You're like that fighter,
Alison.

19:09.065 --> 19:10.858
You're uniquely you.

19:10.858 --> 19:13.694
And you can't really say that
about most people.

19:24.246 --> 19:25.790
Thank you, Marta.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.794
Shouldn't you be back
in Rosewood?

19:32.254 --> 19:34.715
Mm, I'm not leaving.

19:36.008 --> 19:37.885
- Excuse me?
- I'm keeping my job.

19:37.885 --> 19:39.929
That's not how this works.

19:41.222 --> 19:43.015
I know why you fired me.

19:43.015 --> 19:45.601
Because you slept
with a student.

19:45.601 --> 19:48.479
Not just a student. Mason.

19:52.775 --> 19:54.693
Jealous much?

19:56.112 --> 19:57.530
Sorry?

19:57.530 --> 20:02.034
He told me about
how you comforted each other

20:02.034 --> 20:04.703
in your moment of grief
after Nolan's death.

20:26.725 --> 20:29.937
I've decided not to terminate
Mona Vanderwaal.

20:29.937 --> 20:31.856
She'll be staying on with us.

20:34.859 --> 20:36.902
- Thank you.
- It goes without saying--

20:36.902 --> 20:38.946
It won't happen again.

20:40.030 --> 20:42.158
You can see yourself out.

20:59.967 --> 21:01.760
Hey.

21:01.760 --> 21:03.971
There's my little girl.

21:03.971 --> 21:06.223
Don't call me that.

21:06.223 --> 21:07.892
I am not your little girl.

21:07.892 --> 21:10.394
I've been on my own
for over a year now.

21:10.394 --> 21:13.063
What's wrong? What happened?

21:13.063 --> 21:15.858
What happened is
I found out that my dad

21:15.858 --> 21:18.277
is not only a thief

21:18.277 --> 21:20.154
but a liar.

21:20.154 --> 21:22.573
You were just using me
to get to the rest of the money

21:22.573 --> 21:24.241
you stole, weren't you?

21:28.871 --> 21:31.081
You needed
the bank account numbers.

21:31.081 --> 21:33.000
Sealed for legal reasons?

21:39.131 --> 21:40.883
You didn't raise me
to be an idiot.

21:40.883 --> 21:43.093
What'd you do
with the notebook?

21:43.093 --> 21:45.429
- It's not here.
- Did you give it to Booker?

21:45.429 --> 21:47.598
Why would I do that?

21:51.185 --> 21:53.979
'I see how this is working.'

21:53.979 --> 21:55.940
You plan on keeping the money.

22:00.236 --> 22:01.695
You've taken
plenty for you and mom

22:01.695 --> 22:03.405
to live a comfortable life
on the run.

22:03.405 --> 22:05.658
Ava, we're not on the run.
Okay?

22:05.658 --> 22:07.826
We changed our names.
We live in a small town.

22:07.826 --> 22:10.454
It's charming.
I think you'd like it there.

22:10.454 --> 22:12.915
My life is here now..

22:12.915 --> 22:16.085
...with friends
who have become like my family.

22:16.085 --> 22:18.921
But unlike my family,
they won't abandon me

22:18.921 --> 22:22.007
and leave me
to clean up their mess.

22:22.007 --> 22:24.176
And I can actually trust them.

22:27.221 --> 22:29.139
It's a lot of money, Ava.

22:31.100 --> 22:33.561
Too much for you to handle.

22:33.561 --> 22:35.980
- You'll get caught.
- No, I won't.

22:37.064 --> 22:38.649
Because I learned
how to get away

22:38.649 --> 22:41.026
with other people's money
from you.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.323
[sighs]

22:46.323 --> 22:48.158
I'm sorry.

22:49.660 --> 22:51.412
I'm sorry
that I turned you into me.

22:51.412 --> 22:53.789
I am nothing like you.

22:56.875 --> 22:59.044
Don't. Don't.

23:04.258 --> 23:07.219
- I am sorry.
- That makes two of us.

23:23.402 --> 23:25.988
[sobbing]

23:29.700 --> 23:32.870
[bell tolling]

23:45.758 --> 23:47.343
(Ava)
Oh, hey.

23:50.054 --> 23:53.015
- So this is weird.
- Yeah, no kidding.

23:53.015 --> 23:54.475
You're not even a student here.

23:54.475 --> 23:57.436
(Ava)
Are we sure
this is the Crimson Society?

23:57.436 --> 24:00.272
Did we all get an invitation?

24:00.272 --> 24:02.316
- This afternoon.
- Same.

24:03.692 --> 24:05.235
You could have told me.

24:05.235 --> 24:07.154
I wasn't gonna come
but turns out

24:07.154 --> 24:08.989
Claire had a change of heart.

24:08.989 --> 24:11.408
I'm staying,
and you could have told me too.

24:12.951 --> 24:15.371
[TV turns on]

24:15.371 --> 24:17.748
(man on PA system)
'Please take your seats.'

24:19.792 --> 24:21.418
(Alison)
Two empty chairs.

24:22.753 --> 24:24.213
Did you notice?

24:25.839 --> 24:27.466
(Caitlin)
I guess so.

24:27.466 --> 24:28.884
(Dylan)
What the hell?

24:28.884 --> 24:32.054
[dramatic music]

24:39.770 --> 24:42.189
- I trusted you.
- And I trusted you.

24:42.189 --> 24:44.233
- 'To do the right thing.'
- 'Oh, my God.'

24:44.233 --> 24:45.776
- Stop!
- Taylor!

24:45.776 --> 24:48.487
- Jeremy, please stop.
- Don't do it.

24:48.487 --> 24:50.114
[gunshot]

24:52.032 --> 24:54.785
(Caitlin on video)
'Jeremy! Jeremy!'

24:56.453 --> 24:59.456
- 'I'm calling 911.'
- What did you just do?

24:59.456 --> 25:01.291
(Taylor on video)
He was getting away.
He was leaving.

25:01.291 --> 25:02.960
'He was trying to leave
and you saw it.'

25:02.960 --> 25:04.795
(Caitlin on video)
'Oh, my God.'

25:04.795 --> 25:07.548
(Ava on video)
He was charging at you
with something in his hands.

25:07.548 --> 25:10.426
(Taylor on video)
'He killed my brother.
He was getting away.'

25:10.426 --> 25:13.303
- 'He was getting away with it!'
- 'Taylor, calm down!'

25:13.303 --> 25:14.972
[static]

25:14.972 --> 25:16.473
Was that Beacon Guard footage?

25:16.473 --> 25:19.309
- I thought we were off campus.
- Obviously, we weren't.

25:22.146 --> 25:25.315
(man on PA system)
'Welcome to the experiment,
phase two.'

25:26.942 --> 25:30.070
- Who are you?
- What do you want?

25:30.070 --> 25:32.948
[dramatic music]

25:32.948 --> 25:34.491
Why is Beacon Guard
at the river?

25:34.491 --> 25:36.285
The school is always buying
more property

25:36.285 --> 25:38.162
expanding
on their land portfolio.

25:38.162 --> 25:39.621
Are we sure
it was a Beacon Guard camera?

25:39.621 --> 25:41.999
No, we're not sure of anything
right now.

25:41.999 --> 25:43.417
Could this be Dana
still messing with us?

25:43.417 --> 25:45.544
(man on PA system)
'I've been watching you'

25:45.544 --> 25:47.296
'and it's been informative.'

25:47.296 --> 25:49.131
'But now that
you have given me proof'

25:49.131 --> 25:51.383
'that you are guilty
of attempted murder'

25:51.383 --> 25:54.219
'and conspiring
to cover up the crime'

25:54.219 --> 25:56.805
'I can take my experiment
to the next level.'

25:56.805 --> 26:00.058
'Follow instructions
if you want to remain free.'

26:00.058 --> 26:01.894
We're not free
if you're controlling us.

26:01.894 --> 26:04.646
- What experiment?
- Who are you?

26:04.646 --> 26:07.399
(man on PA system)
'I'm the person
who killed Nolan.'

26:07.399 --> 26:09.401
'Jeremy was guilty
of many things'

26:09.401 --> 26:10.861
'but he was not a killer'

26:10.861 --> 26:13.530
'and I didn't take pleasure
in having to become one.'

26:13.530 --> 26:16.575
Oh, my God.
Jeremy didn't kill Nolan.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.911
(man on PA system)
'And like all of you,
Jeremy was part'

26:18.911 --> 26:20.704
'of the experiment part one.'

26:20.704 --> 26:23.999
'He's surveilled you at my
instruction to protect Caitlin.'

26:23.999 --> 26:25.459
'He has served his purpose'

26:25.459 --> 26:27.294
'and he's been removed
from the equation.'

26:27.294 --> 26:29.338
What do you mean removed?

26:29.338 --> 26:31.423
- 'Do as you're told.'
- What do you mean removed?

26:31.423 --> 26:33.967
(man on PA system)
'The Professor
will be watching.'

26:35.135 --> 26:37.304
What is the experiment?

26:39.264 --> 26:41.391
It sounds like phase one
was surveilling us.

26:41.391 --> 26:43.435
So all that stuff
that happened to us

26:43.435 --> 26:44.561
'was that Dana
or the Professor?'

26:44.561 --> 26:45.896
I don't wanna know
what phase two is.

26:45.896 --> 26:47.523
Yes, you do.

26:47.523 --> 26:49.775
You can't win the game
if you don't know the rules.

26:49.775 --> 26:51.360
This isn't a game.

26:51.360 --> 26:53.487
He manipulated us
into almost killing Jeremy.

26:53.487 --> 26:55.697
So we're like
human lab rats now?

26:55.697 --> 26:58.534
This room didn't set itself up
on its own.

26:58.534 --> 27:00.452
We have to get to Taylor..

27:00.452 --> 27:03.622
We're being watched, remember?

27:03.622 --> 27:05.499
Let's get out of here.

27:08.836 --> 27:11.463
(Caitlin)
I just need to talk
to Jeremy Beckett, please.

27:11.463 --> 27:14.174
He has the right
to a phone call. It's the law.

27:14.174 --> 27:17.511
Hello? Hello? Damn it!

27:17.511 --> 27:19.346
Caitlin, he's in a hospital
full of cops, right?

27:19.346 --> 27:21.098
- He's gonna be fine.
- Why us?

27:21.098 --> 27:22.349
What does this person want?

27:22.349 --> 27:24.518
If those are really
Beacon Guard cameras

27:24.518 --> 27:26.270
then Dana and Claire would know
the truth about Jeremy

27:26.270 --> 27:27.479
and we'd all be in jail
right now.

27:27.479 --> 27:28.730
Would we?
It was her daughter

27:28.730 --> 27:30.357
who pulled the trigger.

27:30.357 --> 27:31.775
Taylor told me
that before she disappeared

27:31.775 --> 27:33.944
she discovered that
someone hijacked Beacon Guard

27:33.944 --> 27:36.488
to spy on a select group
of people.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.323
How would she
even figure that out?

27:38.323 --> 27:41.243
Taylor created Beacon Guard..

27:41.243 --> 27:43.036
...after her father
was murdered.

27:43.036 --> 27:45.497
Nobody knows how the system
works better than she does.

27:45.497 --> 27:48.166
Whoever hijacked Beacon Guard
tried to kill Taylor.

27:48.166 --> 27:49.543
That's why she left.

27:49.543 --> 27:51.253
So she knew
somebody was watching us?

27:51.253 --> 27:52.462
No, she knew
people were being watched

27:52.462 --> 27:54.631
but she didn't know
who they were or why.

27:54.631 --> 27:57.217
We don't know the why,
but now we know who we are.

27:57.217 --> 27:59.219
Minus the two
that never showed up tonight.

27:59.219 --> 28:01.221
There were seven chairs
and five of us.

28:01.221 --> 28:02.681
Why wouldn't she tell us
about this?

28:02.681 --> 28:04.808
The scoreboard,
the rat in my trunk

28:04.808 --> 28:06.852
Caitlin getting hit by a car.

28:06.852 --> 28:09.688
Are we saying that this wasn't
Dana poking us until we cracked?

28:09.688 --> 28:13.400
I'd rather believe it's Dana
than this Professor creep.

28:13.400 --> 28:15.569
I think there's someone
in there.

28:18.530 --> 28:21.533
I was out here yesterday
with Taylor.

28:21.533 --> 28:23.452
We did not leave the lights on
when we left.

28:24.745 --> 28:27.122
Maybe it's Taylor.
Maybe she's back from Riverwell.

28:27.122 --> 28:29.583
[dramatic music]

28:29.583 --> 28:32.502
[explosion]

28:39.927 --> 28:42.554
- Is everybody okay?
- Yeah.

28:42.554 --> 28:45.307
Well, if there was somebody
in there

28:45.307 --> 28:47.559
they're in pieces now.

28:47.559 --> 28:49.978
What? It's the truth.

28:49.978 --> 28:53.148
[cell phones ringing]

28:55.859 --> 28:57.611
What?

28:57.611 --> 29:00.072
How could we be calling
ourselves?

29:04.576 --> 29:07.996
I don't know,
but I'm answering it.

29:07.996 --> 29:11.833
(Professor on phone)
'Participation in the experiment
is mandatory.'

29:11.833 --> 29:13.543
'Failure to follow instructions'

29:13.543 --> 29:16.380
'will result in your immediate
incarceration.'

29:24.012 --> 29:25.806
So what do we do now?

29:25.806 --> 29:28.600
We do whatever
the Professor tells us to do.

29:28.600 --> 29:30.727
We keep this to ourselves,
and we play along

29:30.727 --> 29:31.770
until we figure out
who they are.

29:31.770 --> 29:33.438
Great. More secrets.

29:33.438 --> 29:34.564
How are we supposed
to figure out who they are

29:34.564 --> 29:36.358
if they can see
everything we do?

29:36.358 --> 29:38.193
Are you sure we shouldn't
just go to the cops

29:38.193 --> 29:39.611
and tell them the truth?

29:39.611 --> 29:41.446
Do you really wanna
take that risk?

29:41.446 --> 29:43.573
We're all complicit
and it's on video.

29:43.573 --> 29:45.784
'Last I checked,
conspiracy to cover up a felony'

29:45.784 --> 29:47.911
lands you up to five years
in prison.

29:47.911 --> 29:49.538
You check stuff like that?

29:49.538 --> 29:51.623
I get bored in long lines.

29:51.623 --> 29:53.750
And, look, if Jeremy was a part
of the experiment

29:53.750 --> 29:56.044
then maybe you can figure out
the connection

29:56.044 --> 29:57.462
between him and the Professor.

29:57.462 --> 29:58.797
Knowledge is power.

29:58.797 --> 30:01.133
Well, it seems like
the Professor has all of it.

30:01.133 --> 30:02.926
So we take it back.

30:02.926 --> 30:04.428
We stay and we fight.

30:04.428 --> 30:05.554
I'd do whatever it takes
to make sure

30:05.554 --> 30:07.097
no one sees that video.

30:07.097 --> 30:08.640
I didn't work this hard
to reinvent myself

30:08.640 --> 30:10.600
just to become
another wanted Jalali.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.978
I agree. I didn't work this hard
to stay at BHU

30:12.978 --> 30:15.522
just to give up now.

30:15.522 --> 30:16.773
I know where to start.

30:16.773 --> 30:20.110
Does this mean
you're gonna keep seeing him?

30:20.110 --> 30:22.237
Is that why you want it?

30:23.238 --> 30:25.490
Secrets are so hard to keep,
Claire.

30:25.490 --> 30:28.285
The fewer people who know them,
the better.

30:30.120 --> 30:31.538
Mona.

30:36.334 --> 30:38.336
I'm watching you.

30:44.968 --> 30:47.888
[keys clacking]

30:54.186 --> 30:58.732
♪ She said boy you better run
better run better run ♪

30:58.732 --> 31:01.359
Are you sure you wanna do this
right now?

31:01.359 --> 31:03.570
You seem off. Frazzled.

31:03.570 --> 31:06.281
I need to do it today.

31:06.281 --> 31:08.450
I need to know that
I can stand up for myself.

31:08.450 --> 31:09.993
- Okay.
- Yeah.

31:09.993 --> 31:13.914
♪ He said boy you got a gun
got a gun for a tongue ♪

31:13.914 --> 31:15.332
Hey, Luke.

31:15.332 --> 31:16.917
Oh, so, you're back?
You ran out of here--

31:16.917 --> 31:19.419
I don't know why you're here but
I'm not afraid of you anymore.

31:19.419 --> 31:21.505
- Look, Dylan--
- No, listen to me.

31:21.505 --> 31:24.299
You mess with me again
and you will regret it.

31:29.262 --> 31:34.059
♪ But one day I'm gonna rise
from the fire below ♪

31:34.059 --> 31:36.812
♪ I'm coming back
from the dead ♪♪

31:39.648 --> 31:41.066
(Mona)
I got it from Claire.

31:41.066 --> 31:43.527
It's the location of every
active Beacon Guard camera

31:43.527 --> 31:44.903
and listening device

31:44.903 --> 31:47.906
and a list of every dead zone
on the campus.

31:47.906 --> 31:50.659
Places we can talk...privately.

31:50.659 --> 31:52.160
Is this one of them?

31:52.160 --> 31:53.954
